16/02/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The main opposition party New Democracy (ND) is ahead of the ruling PASOK party by 3 per cent, according to the latest poll published Sunday (15 February) in the local newspaper <I>Kathimerini</I>. The survey, conducted by the MRB company, showed ND drawing 39.9 per cent of the votes, followed by PASOK with 36.9 per cent and the Communist Party of Greece with 5.3 per cent. Furthermore, 53.3 per cent of the respondents believe that ND will win the 7 March parliamentary elections. (ANA, Kathimerini - 15/02/04)
